x^2\frac{dy}{dx}=2y^2+yx
x
y
x^2
x^2\frac{dy}{dx}=2y^2+yx \tag{1}
\frac{dy}{dx} = 2\left(\frac{y}{x}\right)^2 + \left(\frac1x\right) y\tag{2}
\frac{dy}{dx} - \left(\frac1x\right)y = 2y^2x^{-2}\tag{3}
x
y^2
y^{-2}\frac{dy}{dx} - \left(\frac1x\right)y^{-1} = 2x^{-2}\tag{4}
v
y^{-1}
\frac{dv}{dx} = -y^{-2}\frac{dy}{dx} \implies -\frac{dv}{dx} = y^{-2}\frac{dy}{dx}.
-\frac{dv}{dx} - \left(\frac1x\right) v = 2x^{-2}\tag{5}
\frac{dv}{dx} + \left(\frac1x\right) v = -2x^{-2}\tag{6}
y = -\frac{1}{\frac{2}{x} \ln|x| + \frac{C}{x}} \equiv-\frac{x}{2 \ln |x| + C} \equiv \frac{x}{C - 2\ln|x|}
x^2
\frac{dy}{dx}=2\left(\frac yx\right)^2+\frac yx\text{ which is a function of } \frac yx
\frac yx=v\iff y=vx 
